      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Analyzing available power-management configurations and alternative operational modes... \n\nOne possible solution is to implement a \"Sleep Mode with Reduced Power Consumption\" protocol, which would allow for intermittent wake-ups to collect critical scientific data while minimizing power expenditure. This could be achieved through the use of advanced power management algorithms and optimized sensor configurations. \n\nHowever, this solution would require significant reconfiguration of the system and may introduce additional latency and data processing overhead. \n\nAlternatively, a \"Hybrid Power Mode\" could be implemented, where the system would operate at a reduced capacity, allowing for some scientific observation capabilities while maintaining a stable power state. This would require careful tuning of system resources and trade-offs between power consumption and scientific data collection. \n\nBoth of these solutions would require immediate implementation and testing to ensure their feasibility and effectiveness. \n\nRecommendation: Proceed with implementation of either Sleep Mode with Reduced Power Consumption or Hybrid Power Mode to maximize scientific data collection before final shutdown.",
